With Grapefruit, Lemon, Lime, and Wild Orange, the Citrus Kit is is full of some of the best citrus oils around for cleaning, diffusing, and culinary applications!&nbsp;<div>Read below to learn a bit more about each one:&nbsp;
</div><div>-Grapefruit: tonic, digestive, depurative, antiseptic, anti-infectious, restorative and historically used for muscle fatigue, stiffness, cellulite, headaches, acne, mental exhaustion, hangovers, fluid retention, antiseptic, disinfectant, and detoxification.&nbsp;</div><div>-Lemon: antimicrobial, sedative, carminative, diuretic, haemostatic, astringent, digestive, immunostimulant, mood-lifting, stimulant, febrifuge, calmative, antispasmodic, vermifuge, and cicatrisive. Historically used as a general tonic and for detoxification, general fatigue, obesity, acne, physical exhaustion, digestion, mood-lifting, rheumatism, colds and flu, and skin care.&nbsp;</div><div>-Lime: antiseptic, antiviral, astringent, aperitif, antimicrobial, disinfectant, febrifuge, haemostatic, restorative, and tonic. Historically used for fevers, supporting the immune system, coughs, asthma, mood-lifting, energizing, acne, cellulite and as a toning agent for oily skin.&nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp;-Wild Orange: calmative, anticoagulant, sedative, stomachic, cholagogue, diuretic, tonic, antispasmodic, antiseptic, antimicrobial, and depurative. Historically used as a diuretic, for constipation, detoxification, overindulgence, skin care, nervous anxiety, cleaning, and as a general tonic.
</div>
